                <h4 class="largeCaption">Symptoms</h4>
                <p class="text">A dermatofibroma usually presents as a solitary firm papule or nodule on a limb.</p>
                <ul class="text">
                    <li>A dermatofibroma usually presents as a solitary firm papule or nodule on a limb.</li>
                    <li>Dermatofibroma size varies from 0.5–1.5 cm diameter; most lesions are 7–10 mm diameter.</li>
                    <li>The overlying skin dimples on pinching the lesion – the dimple or pinch sign.</li>
                    <li>Colour may be pink to light brown in white skin, and dark brown to black in dark skin; some appear paler in the centre.</li>
                    <li>Dermatofibromas do not usually cause symptoms, but they are sometimes painful, tender, or itchy.</li>
