                <h4 class="largeCaption">Treatments</h4>
                <p class="text">A dermatofibroma is harmless and seldom causes any symptoms. Usually, only reassurance is needed. If it is nuisance or causing concern, the lesion can be removed surgically. Recurrence is common as the lesion often extends beyond the clinical margin.</p>
                <p class="text">Cryotherapy, shave biopsy and laser treatments are rarely completely successful.</p>
